"moluccan-cockatoo":{n:"Moluccan Cockatoo",c:"Bird",s:"Cockatoo",sz:"Large",cl:"White & Salmon Pink",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Salmon-crested_cockatoo",d:"One of the largest white cockatoos with a magnificent salmon-pink retractable crest. Native to the Moluccas (Maluku Islands) in Indonesia. Has one of the loudest calls of any parrot. Vulnerable due to habitat loss and trapping. Known for their strong emotional bonds with caretakers.",w:"640-1,025 g",l:"46-52 cm",life:"40-80 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” seeds, nuts, fruit",cs:"Vulnerable"},
"palm-cockatoo":{n:"Palm Cockatoo",c:"Bird",s:"Cockatoo",sz:"Large",cl:"Dark Grey",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Palm_cockatoo",d:"A dramatic cockatoo with smoky-grey plumage, a massive black bill, and bare red cheek patches that flush deeper when excited. Native to New Guinea and northern Australia. The only bird known to use a tool as a musical instrument â€” they drum on tree trunks with sticks during courtship displays.",w:"500-1,100 g",l:"49-68 cm",life:"40-90 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” pandanus nuts, seeds, fruit",cs:"Least Concern"},
