"channel-billed-toucan":{n:"Channel-billed Toucan",c:"Bird",s:"Toucan",sz:"Medium",cl:"Black & Orange",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Channel-billed_toucan",d:"A large toucan with glossy black plumage, a white bib bordered by red, and a spectacular blue-ridged black bill with orange-yellow base. Native to the forests of South America. The channels or grooves along the bill give this species its name. Feeds primarily on fruit but also raids nests for eggs.",w:"300-430 g",l:"46-53 cm",life:"15-20 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Omnivore â€” fruit, insects, eggs",cs:"Least Concern"},
"green-aracari":{n:"Green Aracari",c:"Bird",s:"Toucan",sz:"Small",cl:"Green & Yellow",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Green_aracari",d:"The smallest member of the toucan family with dark green upperparts, a bright yellow belly with a red patch, and a colourful bill marked with black, orange, and yellow. Native to the forests of northeastern South America. Gregarious and often seen in small family groups moving through the canopy.",w:"110-160 g",l:"30-35 cm",life:"15-20 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Omnivore â€” fruit, insects, eggs",cs:"Least Concern"},
