"dusky-lory":{n:"Dusky Lory",c:"Bird",s:"Lory",sz:"Small",cl:"Brown & Orange",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Dusky_lory",d:"A strikingly coloured parrot with a dark brown cap, orange band across the breast, and vivid orange rump. Native to New Guinea. Two colour phases exist â€” an orange phase and a yellow phase. Feeds primarily on nectar and pollen using a specialised brush-tipped tongue.",w:"150-200 g",l:"25-26 cm",life:"20-30 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Nectarivore â€” nectar, pollen, fruit, seeds",cs:"Least Concern"},
"green-naped-lorikeet":{n:"Green-naped Lorikeet",c:"Bird",s:"Lory",sz:"Small",cl:"Green & Red",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Coconut_lorikeet",d:"One of the most colourful parrots with a blue head, green wings and back, orange-red breast, and green nape. Native to Australasia and Indonesia. Highly active and acrobatic, often hanging upside down while feeding on flowers. Their brush-tipped tongue extracts nectar from blossoms.",w:"100-157 g",l:"25-30 cm",life:"15-25 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Nectarivore â€” nectar, pollen, fruit",cs:"Least Concern"},
"ornate-lorikeet":{n:"Ornate Lorikeet",c:"Bird",s:"Lory",sz:"Small",cl:"Green & Red",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Ornate_lorikeet",d:"A beautifully marked lorikeet with green plumage, a red forehead, blue streaking on the head, and orange-yellow breast barring. Native to the forests of Sulawesi in Indonesia. Less commonly seen in aviculture than other lorikeets, making them a special sighting at Birds of Eden.",w:"100-140 g",l:"24-26 cm",life:"15-25 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Nectarivore â€” nectar, pollen, fruit",cs:"Least Concern"},
"red-lory":{n:"Red Lory",c:"Bird",s:"Lory",sz:"Small",cl:"Red & Blue",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Red_lory",d:"A stunning parrot with predominantly bright red plumage, blue patches on the wings and back, and an orange bill. Native to the Moluccas and surrounding islands of Indonesia. One of the most popular lories in aviculture due to their vivid colour and playful personality.",w:"150-185 g",l:"30-31 cm",life:"20-30 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Nectarivore â€” nectar, pollen, fruit",cs:"Least Concern"},
