"patagonian-conure":{n:"Patagonian Conure",c:"Bird",s:"Conure",sz:"Medium",cl:"Olive & Yellow",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Burrowing_parrot",d:"The largest of all conures, also known as the burrowing parrot because it excavates nesting burrows in cliff faces. Olive-green plumage with a yellow belly patch, orange-red lower belly, and white eye-ring. Native to the arid regions of Argentina and Chile. Colonial nesters forming impressive cliff colonies.",w:"240-310 g",l:"40-46 cm",life:"20-40 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” seeds, grain, fruit, roots",cs:"Least Concern"},
"peach-fronted-conure":{n:"Peach-fronted Conure",c:"Bird",s:"Conure",sz:"Small",cl:"Green & Peach",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"Peach-fronted_parakeet",d:"A bright green conure with a distinctive peach-orange forehead and forecrown, blue flight feathers, and a dark bill. Native to the open woodland and savanna of South America east of the Andes. One of the most widely distributed conure species. Hardy and adaptable.",w:"75-95 g",l:"23-26 cm",life:"20-30 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” seeds, fruit, blossoms",cs:"Least Concern"},
