"white-eyed-conure":{n:"White-eyed Conure",c:"Bird",s:"Conure",sz:"Small",cl:"Green & Red",i:"ğŸ¦œ",wp:"White-eyed_parakeet",d:"A predominantly green conure with scattered red feathers on the head and neck, red patches on the wing bend, and a distinctive bare white eye-ring. Native to South America from the Guianas to Argentina. Hardy and adaptable, found in a wide range of habitats from forest to urban areas.",w:"140-180 g",l:"30-33 cm",life:"20-30 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” seeds, fruit, flowers",cs:"Least Concern"},
