"cape-crow":{n:"Cape Crow",c:"Bird",s:"Corvid",sz:"Large",cl:"Black",i:"ğŸ¦…",wp:"Cape_crow",d:"A large, entirely glossy black crow with a slender, slightly curved bill. Native to eastern and southern Africa. Highly intelligent like all corvids, known for problem-solving and using tools. Often seen in agricultural areas and grasslands, foraging in pairs or small groups on the ground.",w:"400-600 g",l:"48-53 cm",life:"15-20 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Omnivore â€” insects, grain, carrion, small vertebrates",cs:"Least Concern"},
"inca-jay":{n:"Inca Jay",c:"Bird",s:"Corvid",sz:"Medium",cl:"Blue & Yellow",i:"ğŸ¦…",wp:"Inca_jay",d:"A spectacular jay with bright blue upperparts, vivid yellow underparts, and a black head and chest. Native to the cloud forests and woodlands of Central and South America. Highly social and vocal, living in noisy family groups. Their bold colours make them one of the most striking members of the corvid family.",w:"65-110 g",l:"27-33 cm",life:"10-15 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Omnivore â€” insects, fruit, eggs, small vertebrates",cs:"Least Concern"},
