"northern-pintail":{n:"Northern Pintail",c:"Bird",s:"Duck",sz:"Medium",cl:"Brown & White",i:"ğŸ¦†",wp:"Northern_pintail",d:"An elegant, slender dabbling duck. Males have a chocolate-brown head, white breast and neck stripe, grey body, and extremely long pointed tail feathers that give the species its name. One of the most widespread ducks in the Northern Hemisphere. Graceful in flight with a distinctive silhouette.",w:"600-1,100 g",l:"51-65 cm",life:"10-20 years",act:"Crepuscular",diet:"Omnivore â€” seeds, grain, aquatic plants, invertebrates",cs:"Least Concern"},
