"rosy-billed-pochard":{n:"Rosy-billed Pochard",c:"Bird",s:"Duck",sz:"Medium",cl:"Dark Brown & Pink",i:"ğŸ¦†",wp:"Rosy-billed_pochard",d:"A large, handsome diving duck native to South America. Males have a striking purple-black head, bright rosy-red bill with a prominent knob at the base, dark breast, and grey flanks. Females are mottled brown with a dark bill. Found in large marshes and lakes, often forming sizeable flocks.",w:"900-1,200 g",l:"51-57 cm",life:"10-15 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Herbivore â€” aquatic plants, seeds",cs:"Least Concern"},
