"common-starling":{n:"Common Starling",c:"Bird",s:"Starling",sz:"Small",cl:"Dark Iridescent",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Common_starling",d:"One of the world's most successful and widespread birds with dark, iridescent plumage that shimmers with green and purple in sunlight, becoming spotted with white in winter. Native to Europe and western Asia. Famous for their spectacular murmurations â€” swirling flocks of thousands performing synchronised aerial displays.",w:"60-96 g",l:"19-23 cm",life:"5-15 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Omnivore â€” insects, fruit, seeds, scraps",cs:"Least Concern"},
