"spotted-dove":{n:"Spotted Dove",c:"Bird",s:"Dove",sz:"Medium",cl:"Brown & Grey",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"Spotted_dove",d:"A graceful dove with a pinkish-brown body and a distinctive black patch with white spots on the back and sides of the neck, giving it its alternative name of lace-necked dove. Native to South and Southeast Asia but widely introduced elsewhere. Their gentle, rhythmic cooing is a familiar sound of Asian gardens.",w:"130-180 g",l:"28-32 cm",life:"10-15 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Granivore â€” seeds, grain, fruit",cs:"Least Concern"},
