"rameron-pigeon":{n:"Rameron Pigeon",c:"Bird",s:"Dove",sz:"Large",cl:"Dark Purple",i:"ğŸ¦",wp:"African_olive_pigeon",d:"A large, dark pigeon with deep purple-maroon plumage, bare yellow eye-patches and bill, and bright yellow legs. Also known as the African olive pigeon. Native to the forests of eastern and southern Africa. Feeds on fruit in the forest canopy, playing an important role in seed dispersal for indigenous trees.",w:"300-450 g",l:"37-42 cm",life:"10-15 years",act:"Diurnal",diet:"Frugivore â€” fruit, berries, olives",cs:"Least Concern"},
